title: Appointments to Hong Kong Council on Smoking and Health
content_text:
p>
    The Government gazetted today (August 10) the re-appointment of Ms Lisa Lau 
    Man-man as Chairman of the Hong Kong Council on Smoking and Health. Three serving members, namely Mr Abraham Chan Yu-ling, Mr Chau Yui-chi and 
    Ms Yolanda Ng Yuen-ting, are re-appointed. In addition, Dr Mak Yiu-kwong, Dr 
    Joyce Tang Shao-fen, Mr Jason Wong Chun-tat and Mr Christopher Yu Wing-fai

are appointed as new Council members.  All the appointments will be effective from October 1, 2012, for a term of 
    two years.  The Hong Kong Council on Smoking and Health is an independent statutory body 
    established in 1987 to advise the Government on matters related to smoking 
    and health. It is also tasked with advancing public education concerning the 
    effects of smoking on the community and individuals as well as engaging in 
    smoking-related research. The full membership of the Council with effect from October 1, 2012, is as

follows: Ms Lisa Lau Man-man (Chairman)
